document_data.Personality:
{{Fq
| text = Bah, life's too short for such worries!
| source = Wakanga O'tamu
}}
He enjoyed life's luxuries, especially pleasures of the flesh. Those who called on him at his villa might find him absorbed in gilded [[book|tomes]] and disinterested in speaking until he had finished his reading.

He was quick to embrace friends of his friends, and if he took an interest in a visitor to Port Nyanzaru, he might grant them certain protections within the city.

Activities.Governance:
{{Fq
| text =   If the prince has taken interest in you, you would do well not to die on your first expedition.
| source = [[Ze'Vana Ritzulma]]
}}
As a merchant prince, Wakanga was part of the council that ruled Port Nyanzaru from the palace of [[Goldenthrone]]. He took it upon himself to hire mercenaries to protect merchant [[ship]]s from pirates (especially those containing his own goods), to send explorers into the jungle in search of trade routes, and to hire [[adventurer]]s to keep the surrounding lands safe. In some cases, adventurers were rewarded for their service with valuable maps from his library.
